==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Pungled
<hw>Pun"gled</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[Etymol.
uncertain.]</ety> <def>Shriveled or shrunken; -- said especially of
grain which has lost its juices from the ravages of insects, such as the
wheat midge, or Trips (<spn>Thrips cerealium</spn>).</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Pungy</ent>⟦br⟧
